reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Tastes great, good quantity, and effective
reviews.reviewText: I bought these Olly vitamins add to my daily routine as I work on making better choices for my body and overall health. I was very impressed by these. I was energetic all day, the taste was pleasant, and the price was very reasonable. It comes with 90 gummies and is a 45 day supply. I decided to order them on a subscription instead of a one time buy so I don't run out. I also bought the Olly Teen Girl gummies for my daughter. Highly recommend this brand!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I have been taking these gummies for over two months and I love them. They are delicious, chewy, and berry-flavored. They make taking vitamins fun and easy. They also make me feel good, as they provide 18 essential nutrients for my overall wellness. I notice that I have more energy and better skin since I started taking them. They are also gluten-free and vegan-friendly, which is important for me. I would highly recommend these gummies to any woman who wants to boost her health and happiness. They are a tasty and healthy treat.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easiest Way to Take Your Vitamins
reviews.reviewText: Great taste, easy to chew! I have a hard time remembering to take pills that don't fit into my kittle pill container. Multivitamins do not come small enough to fit in a little weekly pill container. I kept forgetting to take my daily multivitamin until I found chewable gummy ones. After searching for ones that both don't taste like grass, are easy to chew and have the daily vitamins and minerals I need. I also really like the addition of folic acid and biotin; my moods as well has my hair and nails have gotten noticeably better.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I always take vitamins I am a nurse and i dont want to get sick so i try my best to stay healthy. I have tried many multi vitamins and the pills make me nauseous and alot of gummies have a nasty taste or weird consistency. these have neither. they are easy to chew and taste great. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Expensive, and no iron, but my hair is growing back thicker
reviews.reviewText: I don’t write reviews, unless it’s for an absolutely terrible product, but I wanted to share my 6 month experience with these Olly chewable vitamins.Initially, the taste of the Women’s chewable multi gummy was eh. Kinda fruity but I can tell it’s a vitamin. The smell is NOT fruity and it’s not pleasant(smells like how a typical vitamin tastes if it stays on your tongue too long before you swallow it lol) As time went on the taste has become better, the smell tolerable, and I just think of them as my healthy morning fruit snack.I haven’t taken them consistently over 6 months, I’ll run out and forget to order more for a week or two and sometimes forget to take them for a day or two. But overall, my skin, hair and nails are much happier. The most significant sign of any change has been my hair. It falls out less during washings and with brushing, and I can tell it’s growing back thicker around my hairline. My nails are growing back faster (but not really thicker/stronger) and my skin is less dry.During the summer my order from Amazon came melted, and on another shipment the ice pack they include to prevent the gummies from melting had opened up everywhere. After those instances, I now order directly from the Olly website and haven’t had any issues.I have used their Collagen rings twice during this 6 month period and I’m sure that’s also contributed to my hair and nail growth. The collagen gummies are only a 2 week supply, I wish you could order a 30 day supply. I’ve also used their glowing skin gummies for a month. The tastes and smells of those two gummies are also in the fruity but still vitamin-y category for me. However, it’s a vitamin, not candy. I’m not expecting something sweet.I have also taken their probiotic/prebiotic gummy everyday over the past 4 months, and it has seemed to help regulate everything in my GI tract. (These actually taste and smell great)As someone else mentioned, the Women’s multi gummy does not include iron, which is a bummer, since iron is important for women 🙃Overall I’m happy with these Women’s multi gummies due to my hair regrowth, but I’m sure there is a comparable alternative that is less expensive.
